708021f-b.title: Manhattan: 3rd Avenue - 19th Street
708021f-b.text:
(1)
Third Ave., east side, north from East 19th Street, showing the
Third Ave. Elevated Line. Also seen (in the background), is the Chrysler
Building. Note the Christmas trees displayed on the sidewalk.
DDecember 23, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, from a point several feet northward.
December 23, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

711521f-a.title: Manhattan: 3rd Avenue - 19th Street (East)
711521f-a.text:
148, 6 and 4 East 19th Street, at, adjoining and west of the
S. W. corner of Third Avenue. No. 148 is the 3-story corner hotel
and saloon and is only partially shown. This also bears No. 222
Third Avenue.
About 1915
Gift of E. M. Jenks
